Key Match Events: The Raptors lost to the Milwaukee Bucks with a score of 128-104.
RJ Barrett scored 25 points and grabbed 9 rebounds.
Scottie Barnes contributed 21 points and 5 assists.
Immanuel Quickley added 11 points and 3 assists.
Gary Trent Jr. scored 17 points for the Bucks, making three of five from three-point range.
Pre-Game Insights: Coach Darko Rajakovic emphasized the need to observe and learn what the new group can bring, stating it would take time for the players to start clicking.
Post-Match Reflections: RJ Barrett expressed the need for the team to play harder and improve their performance.
Coach Darko Rajakovic highlighted the lack of connection and fight in the team, noting the need for more sample size to evaluate the new lineup.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The game marked the first time Immanuel Quickley, Scottie Barnes, and RJ Barrett played together this season.
Toronto was significantly outscored from beyond the three-point line, 66-27.
Gary Trent Jr. signed a one-year, $2.6-million deal with the Bucks after leaving the Raptors.
